{"type": "article", "id": 55484, "title": "肩颈酸痛？来试下这款可塞入钱包的迷你按摩仪｜这个设计了不起", "description": "我们每天都为你推荐几个最近发现的好设计。", "date": "2018-07-22T23:01:01Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [{"id": 271, "name": "工业设计"}, {"id": 768, "name": "产品设计"}, {"id": 52036, "name": "LEXON"}, {"id": 52037, "name": "by TextielMuseum"}, {"id": 28073, "name": "Scholten & Baijings"}, {"id": 16231, "name": "Marc Venot"}, {"id": 52038, "name": "Nate McCracken"}, {"id": 52039, "name": "Masahiko Ito"}, {"id": 52040, "name": "Katalin Huszár"}], "category": 17, "column": 38, "author": 1329, "comment_count": 13, "praise_count": 189, "image": "img/article/article_show/20180722214410LkPTBVKgDAd4qyIn.jpg", "contents": "<p nocleanhtml=\"true\">        <style type=\"text/css\"> p.p1 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 11.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #000000; -webkit-text-stroke: #000000} p.p2 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 11.0px Helvetica; color: #000000; -webkit-text-stroke: #000000} p.p3 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 18.0px; font: 16.0px Times; color: #444444; -webkit-text-stroke: #444444; background-color: #ffffff; min-height: 19.0px} span.s1 {font-kerning: none} span.s2 {font: 11.0px Helvetica; font-kerning: none} span.s3 {font: 11.0px 'PingFang SC'; font-kerning: none} span.s4 {text-decoration: underline ; font-kerning: none} span.s5 {font-kerning: none; color: #657ab7; -webkit-text-stroke: 0px #657ab7} span.s6 {font: 11.0px Helvetica; font-kerning: none; color: #657ab7; -webkit-text-stroke: 0px #657ab7} </style>  </p><p>「这个设计了不起」的微信公众号上线啦，直接搜索「BestDesign」或是「Qthings」就可以订阅，关注我们每日发现的新鲜好设计。</p><h3>Cardlax</h3><p>每天下班、放学后，拖着一身疲累的身躯回家，窝在沙发或床上休息时，有些僵硬酸疼的肌肉部位总想用按摩的方式来加速复原。除了直接按压肌肉部位的物理性按摩方式，还有一种用凝胶电极贴片贴在皮肤上，导入微电流刺激神经系统，达到放松肌肉、舒缓酸痛的效果。</p><p>比如这款最近在众筹网站 Kickstarter 网站上线的 Cardlax 卡片式按摩仪，机身如信用卡大小，能够塞入钱包，使用者无论何时何地都能让自己放松一下，尽快消除疲劳。</p><p>内置的 140mH 可充电电池约可使用 10 小时之久，通过 Micro USB 连接线充电，另有蓝牙连线装置。Cardlax上方有四组按钮，分别是开关、模式、力道加强以及力道减弱功能，使用时有揉、捏、压三种模式可调节，凝胶贴片可以水洗后重复使用。</p><div class=\"com-insert-embed com-insert-embeds\">\r\n\t<figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n\t\t<iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"https://v.qq.com/iframe/player.html?vid=g0638e09pzy&amp;tiny=0&amp;auto=0\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe>\r\n\t</figure>\r\n\t\r\n</div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214453TC8a5rh3ZGcMDOtN.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/2018072221445384drsYytc5jxogvW.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214453CSFeqmdwTsutxDvZ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667619\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214454btU7oeBCSLnA6cK8.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214454Ei9FQcOa6syYwN2K.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214454c9ESepbBtgLlIKHW.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667619\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214455kXdy0Zc4GDNYaU6B.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Notjustuseless by Katalin Huszár </h3><p>匈牙利时装设计师 Katalin Huszár 最近推出了一个名为 Notjustuseless 的项目，试图引发人们对塑料垃圾问题的关注。他希望实验一中创新的收集塑料吸管的方式，进行再次利用，设计出多种面料，可制成窗帘、隔断或者桌布。</p><p>在这个项目中，消费者可以将使用过的塑料吸管放入附近专为项目目标设计的容器中进行回收，而不是直接丢弃。收集箱上印有二维码，扫描二维码便可进入项目页面，方便参与者跟进整个过程。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214534u2fXq7xEYnBGslFk.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.493888\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201807222145348TQsZhGBm1DyNPSW.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.493888\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201807222145346F0sbLwIXZEBDtyg.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.372861\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214534CQ2S5f0teuBmbP3a.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.500000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/2018072221453430fHhZpUq2PJFDxK.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.500000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214534M0DUBqgFlmeQ3hCs.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.500000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214536xMcabOm25Xnl4LKF.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.500000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\">图片来源：<a href=\"http://www.katalinhuszar.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Katalin Huszár</a></figcaption></figure></div><h3>Saddle Seat by Masahiko Ito</h3><p>金斯顿艺术学院的毕业生 Masahiko Ito 为学龄前儿童设计了一把马鞍形椅子 Saddle Seat，试图改善儿童姿势。Saddle Seat 采用窄窄的弯曲的椅身，类似于马鞍的形状，在辅助儿童练习正确坐姿的同时，鼓励其运动，希望能够在一定程度上集中注意力。</p><p>在设计椅子时，Masahiko Ito 研究了姿势和注意力之间的关系，他注意到孩子们在认真听老师讲课时，往往是一种稍前倾的骑行姿势。Saddle Seat 的结构鼓励孩子们坐直，Ito 认为这对于保持坐下时的兴趣和注意力很重要。</p><p>该产品由三个部分组成：座椅、框架和背部。框架由一根连续的钢管制成，有粉色、蓝色和橙色可供选择。座椅由油桦木胶合板制成，而背部由实心木材制成。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214619xRdG0v9yBF1oc8k2.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667513\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214619coIQs54AadY7fM3C.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.562793\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214619pQPSKs2I1Fq7hefA.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667090\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201807222146206pNStrJgqM4iA2Pe.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.498731\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/2018072221461961dMXPNGqkCtKyQs.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.562183\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214621kHQgyDcpxjTXItdv.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666244\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\">图片来源：<a href=\"https://www.dezeen.com/2018/07/20/masahiko-ito-kingston-school-art-school-chair-saddle-seat-furniture-design/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Dezeen</a></figcaption></figure></div><h3>Grid Knit Cushions by Scholten &amp; Baijings for by TextielMuseum</h3><p>荷兰设计工作室 Scholten &amp; Baijings 最近与纺织品牌 by TextielMuseum 合作，推出了一系列垫子 Grid Knit ，特色在于可能会让人看得眼晕的网格状图案。</p><p>Scholten &amp; Baijings 使用 TextielLab 的电脑编织机制作了 Grid Knit 靠垫，色彩缤纷的网格，类似于链条围栏，由包括荧光色在内的各种颜色制成，原材料是 100％ 美利奴羊毛。</p><p>此外，Grid Knit 还将成为 Simply Scandinavian – Nordic Design 1945-2018 展览的一部分。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214720bYOade1hSgoJwQn7.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666406\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214720f3b75x4jqVuSgGiP.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666406\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214720qxN8CzahD32ESjXV.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.798438\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214720wp0A2b7xoesjKSrR.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666406\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214720eaC6jxI3DhS5Wufo.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666406\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214721e6xYbzSi1GJMWI4B.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.715625\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214722IVNkoUz3HxAMetyO.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.328125\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\">图片来源：<a href=\"https://by.textielmuseum.nl/en/service/about/\" rel=\"nofollow\">by TextielMuseum</a></figcaption></figure></div><h3>Cloud Umbrella by Nate McCracken</h3><p>Cloud Umbrella 是一把不会占据用户任何一只手的人体工学伞。在设计师 Nate McCracken 看来，人们使用他们肘部的情况比想象得更多。在风雨雪天气，多带一把伞，就会避免遇上很多狼狈时刻。</p><p>Nate McCracken 设计的这把云伞，试图解放用户的双手，让其固定在夹紧的肘部位置，设有微调空间，意味着任何人都可以找到较为舒适的角度。不使用它时也可以环绕在手腕上。最重要的是，它的设计使其可以悬挂在任何桌子或其他表面上，方便其干燥。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214815KXlOP6gqky9tTD5p.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214815rUsnkdWcQHfGlBqI.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.435238\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214815uv6UE5jq3GLe8Cc4.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201807222148396o2Sv8EUDkIt4Qwp.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.476190\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\">图片来源：<a href=\"http://www.yankodesign.com/2018/07/19/an-umbrella-you-can-actually-handle/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Yanko Design</a></figcaption></figure></div><h3>SECRET Box by Marc Venot for LEXON</h3><p>法国工业设计师 Marc Venot 与法国设计师商品品牌 LEXON 合作，推出 SECRET Box。这是一个令人惊叹的有趣的交互式设计。它很俏皮，简单的 180° 翻转技巧就改变了一个罐子的用途。</p><p>SECRET Box 允许用户将贵重物品存放在透明的丙烯酸罐中。翻转罐子，它从透明变为完全不透明，将你存储的贵重物品隐藏起来。玄机藏在双层容器壁内的不透明乳状液体。当容器保持直立时，液体位于罐子的底部，杯壁保持透明。翻转罐子，液体会填满杯壁，挡住罐子里面的东西。</p><div class=\"com-insert-embed com-insert-embeds\">\r\n\t<figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n\t\t<iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"https://v.qq.com/iframe/player.html?vid=u0731ipg5zb&amp;tiny=0&amp;auto=0\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe>\r\n\t</figure>\r\n\t\r\n</div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214936iwSjvTQpUaMuPFI8.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.706667\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214936v2mlfIdN1PxnYyCZ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667619\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214938WY42yLCVQbizwohs.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667619\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214938JFjfDrbqK6tkoB0I.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.800000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214938BHVmpAyWGeh2ZX7d.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.707619\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180722214939QcqnkCgdHOBL1N28.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667619\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div>"}